Dread Vanguard									KEY:Paladin Archetype ~ Dread Vanguard			CATEGORY:Archetype		TYPE:Archetype.AntipaladinArchetype.PaladinSpells.PaladinAuraOfSin																									PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=1	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Antipaladin Archetype ~ Dread Vanguard],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,TYPE.AntipaladinSpells.AuraOfSin]																			DESC:Some antipaladins serve or ally themselves with villains who are bent on earthly conquest. They care nothing for the intricacies of divine spellcasting, but malevolent energy still surrounds them.																																																																										ABILITY:Antipaladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Dread Vanguard ~ Beacon of Evil|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=4	ABILITY:Antipaladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Dread Vanguard ~ Dark Emissary|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=14																																																																										COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.22	ASPECT:Archetype Base Class|Antipaladin
Beacon of Evil									KEY:Dread Vanguard ~ Beacon of Evil				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AntipaladinClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.PaladinSpells																																																																							DESC:A dread vanguard unleashes the powers of his vile masters to strengthen both himself and his allies. He can use his touch of corruption ability to manifest the darkness in his soul as an area of flickering shadows with a 30-foot radius centered on him. This area provides bonuses to the dread vanguard and his allies based on his level. This ability replaces the dread vanguard's ability to cast spells																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.22
Dark Emissary									KEY:Dread Vanguard ~ Dark Emissary				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AntipaladinClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike.PaladinAuraOfSin																																																																							DESC:A dread vanguard is a true messenger of the forces of darkness he serves. He dread vanguard can use his touch of corruption ability to mark a location with the stain of evil. This location can be any point in space, but the ability works best if placed on an altar, shrine, or other site important to a community. The location is affected as if by a desecrate spell and possibly other horrific effects.																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.22


